listitem.para:
							Web View로 전달할 데이터만 리턴하는 경우
							Model
							은 Java-5 이상에서 사용할 수 있는 인터페이스이다. 기본적으로 ModelMap과 같은 기능을 제공한다. Model
							인터페이스의 구현클래스에는
							BindingAwareModelMap
							 와
							ExtendedModelMap
							 이 있다. View 이름은 위에서 설명한 바와 같이 RequestToViewNameTranslator에 의해 내부적으로
							생성된다.

							When data only to return with web view is returned, 
							Model 
							is an interface that can be used from Java 5 onwards. Functions such as ModelMap are basically provided. 
							There are BindingAwareModelMap and
							ExtendedModelMap 
							in model interface implementation class. 
							View name is internally created by RequestToViewNameTranslator as explained above.

                            @RequestMapping("/movieList.do")
public Model getMovieList() {
    List movieList = movieService.getMovieList();
    ExtendedModelMap map = new ExtendedModelMap();
    map.addAttribute("movieList",movieList);
    return map;
}

							When returning only view name.
                            @RequestMapping(value = {"/addMovie.do", "/updateMovie.do" })
public String updateMovie(Movie movie, SessionStatus status) 
        throws Exception {
    // ...
    return"/listMovie.do";
}

								When HTTP Response is directly handled in method, 
							or when view name is internally created through RequestToViewNameTranslator.
                             @RequestMapping("/addView.do")
public void addView(HttpServletResponse response) {
    // ...
    //Directly handle response
}


							 @RequestMapping("/addView.do")
public void addView() {
    // ...
    // View name is internally defined as 'addView' through DefaultRequestToViewNameTranslator.
}

							When sending return object of handler method directly to Response HTTP Body. 
							Return object is converted through	HttpMessageConverter and returned to response.				
                            @RequestMapping(value = "/welcome", method = RequestMethod.GET)
@ResponseBody
public String welcome() {
    return "Welcome!";
}

							Can be used to access Response HTTP Body and Header on handler method. 
							Body of HttpEntity or ResponseEntity is converted into response stream through HttpMessageConverter.		
                            @RequestMapping(value = "/welcome", method = RequestMethod.GET)
@ResponseBody
public String welcome() {
    return "Welcome!";
}

section.para:
				@RequestParam annotation is used to bind HTTP Request parameter to argument of controller method.
				The role it performs is the same as ServletRequest.getParameter(java.lang.String
					name)

				The following is an example of using @RequestParam annotation.
                @RequestMapping("/updateMovie.do")
public String updateMovie(@RequestParam("movieId") String movieId,         
        @RequestParam("sellAmount") int sellAmount, @RequestParam("realImageFile") MultipartFile picturefile) {
    // ...
    return "/listMovie.do";
}

			    However, when setting required property of @RequestParam as false as below, 
				exception does not occur even when parameter does no exist in HTTP Request. 
                @RequestMapping("/deleteMovie.do")
public String deleteMovie(@RequestParam(value="movieId", required="false") String movieId){
    // ...
}

